    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Authenticating Calls to the ClassKit Catalog API"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You authenticate the calls you make to the ClassKit Catalog API by including a cryptographically signed ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". You sign the JWT using a private key that you provision in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " website, and then include the signed token as part of the header of each call that you make.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Register-a-Private-Key",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Register a Private Key",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Sign in to the Apple Developer web site, and navigate to the “Certificates, IDs, & Profiles” page. Choose Keys in the sidebar, and then click the plus (+) button to add a new key. Name the key, and enable it for use with ClassKit Catalog. Complete the registration and download the private key.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "media-3675465",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can download the private key only once. Apple doesn’t keep a copy of your key, so you can’t retrieve the key again. If you lose your key, you’ll need to revoke the key and create a new one. Similarly, if your private key is ever compromised, you’ll need to revoke the original key and create a new one.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Create-and-Sign-a-Token",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Create and Sign a Token",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Compose a JWT as a combination of a header, a claim set, and a signature, as described in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519",
              "isActive": true,
              "overridingTitle": "JSON Web Token (JWT)",
              "overridingTitleInlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "JSON Web Token (JWT)",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " specification. Create the header as a JSON object with key-value pairs representing:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The key identifier, given by the ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "kid",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " key. Provide the key identifier reported to you by the Apple Developer site after provisioning the key.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The type of token, given by the ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "typ",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " key. Provide a value of ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "JWT",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " to indicated a JSON web token.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The algorithm used to sign the token, given by the ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "alg",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " key. Set the value to ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "ES256",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " to indicate the Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm (ECDSA) algorithm with the P-256 curve and SHA-256 hash algorithm.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "An example header looks like this:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "{",
            "  \"kid\": \"9QVIE72P19\",",
            "  \"typ\": \"JWT\",",
            "  \"alg\": \"ES256\"",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "json",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Create a claim set as another JSON object with key-value pairs representing:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The issuer claim that identifies you as the issuer of the JWT, given by the ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "iss",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " key. Provide your Apple Developer account team identifier as the value.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The issued-at claim that indicates when you created the JWT, given by the ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "iat",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " key. Indicate the number of seconds after the Unix epoch when you created the token.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The expiration-time claim that indicates a time after which the JWT is no longer valid, given by the ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "exp",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " key. Indicate the number of seconds after the Unix epoch when the token should expire, which is typically 10 to 30 minutes after creation.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "An example claim set looks like this:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "{",
            "  \"iss\": \"4J2MBDPZ6M\",",
            "  \"iat\": 1587058400,",
            "  \"exp\": 1587060200",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "json",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Base-64 encode and compute a signature over these two objects, as described in the JWT specification, using your private key with the P-256 ECDSA algorithm and a SHA-256 hash. The two encoded objects plus the computed signature, separated by periods, make up the JWT.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Authenticate-Requests-with-the-Signed-Token",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Authenticate Requests with the Signed Token",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Include the JWT with every request you make to the ClassKit Catalog API by adding ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Authorization: Bearer <JWT>",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to the header, where you replace <",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "JWT>",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " with your actual token. Here is an example of making a request using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "curl",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " command line utility:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "% curl -v -H \"Authorization: Bearer <JWT>\" \"https://classkit-catalog.apple.com/v1/contexts?identifierPath=%5B%22com.apple.www.Quizzer%22%5D&environment=production&locale=en-us\""
          ],
          "syntax": "shell",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
